snippet.textDisplay:
I would love to see a custom HMMWV (Humvee) done by you guys. That would be a great addition to this project. As for layout, people usually do like a U shaped dinette in the end, but I have always thought that a Murphy bed is a great use of space, and then have a table and chairs that you can put away when you don't need them. Another option is a drop down bed from the ceiling like they have in toy haulers. Are you thinking of plumbing in a galley or bathroom? If so, PEX pipe is an easy way to do that and you could do a composting toilet to reduce the size of a needed blackwater tank. An outside shower (with a pop up privacy screen) and kitchen is also a cool idea if you put an awning on the side you want the kitchen on. If you are into racing, the top of that would make a great 'raceday living room'!

Man I am loving the build options you have with this blank canvas! Can't wait to see what you do with it all.
snippet.textOriginal:
I would love to see a custom HMMWV (Humvee) done by you guys.  That would be a great addition to this project.  As for layout, people usually do like a U shaped dinette in the end, but I have always thought that a Murphy bed is a great use of space, and then have a table and chairs that you can put away when you don't need them.  Another option is a drop down bed from the ceiling like they have in toy haulers.  Are you thinking of plumbing in a galley or bathroom?  If so, PEX pipe is an easy way to do that and you could do a composting toilet to reduce the size of a needed blackwater tank.  An outside shower (with a pop up privacy screen) and kitchen is also a cool idea if you put an awning on the side you want the kitchen on.  If you are into racing, the top of that would make a great 'raceday living room'!

Man I am loving the build options you have with this blank canvas!  Can't wait to see what you do with it all.
